<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ890731-0030 </DOCNO><DD> = 890731 </DD><AN> 890731-0030. </AN><HL> LTV Unit Gets Airplane Job </HL><DD> 07/31/89 </DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J) </SO><CO> LTV BBD.A </CO><DATELINE> DALLAS  </DATELINE><TEXT>   LTV Corp., a steel, aerospace and energy concern, said its LTV Aircraft Products Group received a $36 million contract from the Canadair division of Bombardier Inc., Montreal, to build aircraft engine housings.    The housings, known as nacelles, will be used on Canadair's new 50-passenger Regional Jet. The contract calls for LTV to design and produce 106 nacelles to be used on 53 flight test and production aircraft. </TEXT></DOC>